HEADWORD: Celibacy
<hw>Ce*lib"a*cy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Celibate</er>, <pos>n.</pos>]</ety> <def>The state of being
unmarried; single life, esp. that of a bachelor, or of one bound by vows
not to marry.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧The <xex>celibacy</xex> of the clergy.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Hallom.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

